              <DefinitionShort>to come to a point of being visible, with focus upon the process of becoming seen</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to come to be seen</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to appear</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to come into view</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In a number of languages there may be difficulties involved in speaking of ‘the kingdom of God appearing.’ It may not be difficult to speak of a ‘person appearing,’ because an individual may ‘show himself’ or ‘cause himself to be seen.’ It may therefore be necessary to render this expression in {S:04201901100048} as ‘that soon people will be seeing the kingdom of God’ or ‘… experiencing the kingdom of God’ or ‘… become aware of the kingdom of God.’</Comments>
